1
00:00:00,968 --> 00:00:02,970
♪

2
00:00:04,438 --> 00:00:07,675
Woman: Ah, my,
that looks quite good on you.

3
00:00:07,708 --> 00:00:09,410
In all my years,

4
00:00:09,443 --> 00:00:12,146
i’ve never received such
a strange request for clothing,

5
00:00:12,179 --> 00:00:14,548
but the pleasure was mine, sir.

6
00:00:14,581 --> 00:00:16,450
Jotaro: Here. I gotta go.

7
00:00:16,483 --> 00:00:18,952
Keep the change.

8
00:00:18,986 --> 00:00:20,588
See ya.

9
00:00:20,621 --> 00:00:23,557
Woman: Uh, thank you, sir.

10
00:00:23,590 --> 00:00:26,126
( Anne squeals ) Let go!

11
00:00:26,159 --> 00:00:28,962
Let go of me! And don’t you
dare touch me there, you jerk!

12
00:00:28,996 --> 00:00:30,564
Polnareff: Hey,
don’t say it like that.

13
00:00:30,597 --> 00:00:33,033
- Kakyoin: Here’s her ticket.
- Anne: No! I don’t wanna!

14
00:00:33,066 --> 00:00:35,101
I wanna keep going
with you guys! Eh?

15
00:00:35,135 --> 00:00:38,639
Joseph: Listen, little miss.
We’re not vacationing here.

16
00:00:38,672 --> 00:00:40,474
My daughter, jotaro’s mother,

17
00:00:40,507 --> 00:00:42,509
is in grave danger
at the moment.

18
00:00:42,543 --> 00:00:43,544
( Anne gasps )

19
00:00:43,577 --> 00:00:44,711
Joseph: We’re on this journey

20
00:00:44,745 --> 00:00:46,413
to save my daughter’s life,

21
00:00:46,446 --> 00:00:48,515
not to put yours at risk.

22
00:00:48,549 --> 00:00:50,284
Forget this
running-away business,

23
00:00:50,317 --> 00:00:51,552
and start heading home.

24
00:00:51,585 --> 00:00:53,654
I’m sure your parents
are worried sick

25
00:00:53,687 --> 00:00:55,022
wondering where you are.

26
00:00:55,055 --> 00:00:56,323
Polnareff: There.

27
00:00:56,356 --> 00:00:58,258
Anne: Fine. I suppose so.

28
00:00:58,292 --> 00:01:01,095
I’ll make you look good
this time, grandpa.

29
00:01:02,629 --> 00:01:03,763
Huh?

30
00:01:03,797 --> 00:01:06,233
Joseph: Hmm? What’s the matter?

31
00:01:06,266 --> 00:01:08,769
( Anne grunts ) Nothing.

32
00:01:10,304 --> 00:01:14,375
See ya! Life is just
a bunch of goodbyes anyway.

33
00:01:17,211 --> 00:01:20,281
I do sort of wish
I could have seen him once more

34
00:01:20,314 --> 00:01:21,782
before I had to go.

35
00:01:21,815 --> 00:01:22,783
Huh?

36
00:01:22,816 --> 00:01:25,052
( Laughs )

37
00:01:25,085 --> 00:01:27,087
♪

38
00:01:31,258 --> 00:01:33,327
Goodbye, jojo!

39
00:01:33,360 --> 00:01:36,530
You better save your mom!
We’re all counting on you!

40
00:01:36,563 --> 00:01:38,832
I’ll be cheering you on!

41
00:01:43,637 --> 00:01:44,771
Jotaro: Hmph.

42
00:01:44,805 --> 00:01:46,807
♪

43
00:01:54,147 --> 00:01:56,149
( Singing in Japanese )

44
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:31,085
♪

45
00:02:31,118 --> 00:02:33,087
Narrator: Pakistan
is a young country,

46
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:37,524
established in 1947 following
its separation from India.

47
00:02:37,558 --> 00:02:40,261
But when Japan was still
a hunter-gatherer culture,

48
00:02:40,294 --> 00:02:44,298
Pakistan was the seat of
a highly-developed civilization.

49
00:02:44,331 --> 00:02:46,800
Here in Pakistan,
the people carry on

50
00:02:46,834 --> 00:02:50,838
the 5,000-year history
of the Indian subcontinent.

51
00:02:54,875 --> 00:02:56,710
Joseph: I gotta say, jotaro,

52
00:02:56,743 --> 00:02:59,446
i’m impressed you got
a Japanese school uniform

53
00:02:59,479 --> 00:03:01,114
made here in Pakistan.

54
00:03:01,148 --> 00:03:03,150
The fit is perfect, too.

55
00:03:03,183 --> 00:03:05,185
Jotaro: It’s 100% wool.

56
00:03:05,219 --> 00:03:08,189
Kakyoin: Hey, polnareff,
are you okay driving right now?

57
00:03:08,222 --> 00:03:10,825
The fog in this area
is getting quite thick.

58
00:03:10,858 --> 00:03:14,228
Polnareff: These aren’t exactly
the safest conditions.

59
00:03:14,261 --> 00:03:16,864
It’s one hell of a drop
off the right side,

60
00:03:16,897 --> 00:03:19,233
and there’s
no guardrail anywhere.

61
00:03:19,266 --> 00:03:22,836
Joseph: Hmm. The fog looks
even thicker up ahead.

62
00:03:22,870 --> 00:03:27,375
It’s not even 3:00 yet,
but we should head in.

63
00:03:27,407 --> 00:03:30,744
Let’s find a place to stay
in that town for the night.

64
00:03:30,777 --> 00:03:33,346
Polnareff: Do you think
they have nice hotels?

65
00:03:33,380 --> 00:03:34,615
Kakyoin: A nice hotel, huh?

66
00:03:34,648 --> 00:03:35,883
Polnareff: That’s right,

67
00:03:35,916 --> 00:03:37,785
and it’d better have
a decent bathroom.

68
00:03:37,818 --> 00:03:40,888
I--i just couldn’t get used
to the really strange toilets

69
00:03:40,921 --> 00:03:43,657
they have all over India
and the middle east.

70
00:03:45,659 --> 00:03:46,660
( Jotaro gasps )

71
00:03:49,296 --> 00:03:51,665
What the hell?
Was that a dead dog?

72
00:03:51,698 --> 00:03:53,266
Joseph:
What’s the matter, jotaro?

73
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:54,268
Jotaro: Hmm?

74
00:03:54,301 --> 00:03:56,737
Oh. Uh, it was nothing.

75
00:03:56,770 --> 00:03:57,871
Joseph: Hmm?

76
00:04:03,644 --> 00:04:06,614
Hey, this is a nice little town,
don’t you think?

77
00:04:06,647 --> 00:04:07,882
There must be at least

78
00:04:07,915 --> 00:04:11,919
a few thousand people
living here. Eh?

79
00:04:11,952 --> 00:04:14,455
Kakyoin: Let’s ask about a hotel
at that restaurant over there.

80
00:04:18,892 --> 00:04:22,462
Polnareff: But there’s
a weird quiet about this place.

81
00:04:22,496 --> 00:04:23,964
No matter where we’ve gone,

82
00:04:23,997 --> 00:04:26,833
every other place
has been rowdy and congested.

83
00:04:26,867 --> 00:04:29,470
Joseph: It’s probably
because of the fog.

84
00:04:30,604 --> 00:04:31,872
Listen up, guys.

85
00:04:31,905 --> 00:04:34,474
In Pakistan and the rest
of the islamic world,

86
00:04:34,508 --> 00:04:36,477
this is how you greet people.

87
00:04:36,510 --> 00:04:38,679
First, you smile and say...

88
00:04:38,712 --> 00:04:42,282
"As-salaam alaikum."

89
00:04:43,317 --> 00:04:44,685
♪

90
00:04:44,718 --> 00:04:46,486
Eh...

91
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:50,791
( Gasps )

92
00:04:54,428 --> 00:04:55,863
( Grunts )

93
00:04:58,765 --> 00:05:00,867
Uh, no harm intended.
( Chuckles )

94
00:05:00,901 --> 00:05:03,604
No need to close up shop
just for us, sir.

95
00:05:03,637 --> 00:05:05,873
We just wanted
to ask a question.

96
00:05:05,906 --> 00:05:08,442
Are there any hotels
here in town?

97
00:05:08,475 --> 00:05:10,477
♪

98
00:05:15,048 --> 00:05:16,550
Uh...

99
00:05:16,583 --> 00:05:18,452
Anybody home?

100
00:05:19,486 --> 00:05:20,654
Man: I do not know.

101
00:05:20,687 --> 00:05:21,855
- Joseph: Huh?
- Man: Good day.

102
00:05:21,889 --> 00:05:23,424
Joseph: Hey, wait a minute!

103
00:05:23,457 --> 00:05:25,859
What do you mean,
you don’t know? Huh?

104
00:05:28,795 --> 00:05:30,630
( Gasps )

105
00:05:36,069 --> 00:05:37,771
Huh? What’s with that guy?

106
00:05:37,804 --> 00:05:38,772
That can’t be right.

107
00:05:38,805 --> 00:05:40,774
I must have imagined it.

108
00:05:40,807 --> 00:05:42,976
Polnareff: I’m sure
he couldn’t understand you,

109
00:05:43,010 --> 00:05:44,645
because
your pronunciation’s so bad.

110
00:05:44,678 --> 00:05:47,381
Let’s just go ask
that guy over there.

111
00:05:47,414 --> 00:05:49,616
Excuse me. Sorry,

112
00:05:49,650 --> 00:05:51,452
but we’re looking
for a hotel around here,

113
00:05:51,485 --> 00:05:53,921
preferably a hotel
with nice, clean bathrooms.

114
00:05:53,954 --> 00:05:55,656
Do you know any that--

115
00:05:55,689 --> 00:05:56,657
( gasps )

116
00:05:56,690 --> 00:05:58,725
♪

117
00:06:00,694 --> 00:06:02,829
Whoa! Hey, you, what’s wrong?!

118
00:06:09,870 --> 00:06:11,105
All: What the hell?!

119
00:06:13,340 --> 00:06:14,575
Polnareff: He’s dead!

120
00:06:14,608 --> 00:06:16,743
With that look of fear
on his face.

121
00:06:16,777 --> 00:06:17,845
Wh-what’s going on?

122
00:06:17,878 --> 00:06:20,514
Why is he
lying dead in the road?

123
00:06:20,547 --> 00:06:23,316
What could have killed him,
a heart attack?

124
00:06:23,350 --> 00:06:25,319
A stroke?

125
00:06:25,352 --> 00:06:27,454
Jotaro: It’s possible, but look.

126
00:06:27,487 --> 00:06:30,457
What we’ve got here
is no ordinary heart failure.

127
00:06:30,490 --> 00:06:31,725
Polnareff: Huh?

128
00:06:31,758 --> 00:06:34,060
( Gasps ) It’s a gun.

129
00:06:34,094 --> 00:06:36,797
Wait a minute.
This guy’s holding a gun!

130
00:06:36,830 --> 00:06:38,432
Kakyoin: You just noticed?

131
00:06:38,465 --> 00:06:40,867
Jotaro: Check it out.
It’s still smoking.

132
00:06:40,901 --> 00:06:42,770
Joseph: He must have
just fired it,

133
00:06:42,803 --> 00:06:45,005
maybe two to five minutes ago.

134
00:06:45,038 --> 00:06:47,407
Either way, he must have died

135
00:06:47,441 --> 00:06:49,476
right before
we arrived in town.

136
00:06:50,878 --> 00:06:52,913
Polnareff: Do you think
he shot himself?

137
00:06:52,946 --> 00:06:54,581
Kakyoin: No, I doubt it.

138
00:06:54,615 --> 00:06:57,017
His body doesn’t seem
to have any visible wounds,

139
00:06:57,050 --> 00:06:58,652
and there’s no blood anywhere.

140
00:06:58,685 --> 00:06:59,886
Polnareff:
Then how’d this guy die?

141
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:01,655
This isn’t natural. Look at him!

142
00:07:01,688 --> 00:07:05,759
His face is all twisted, like he
was screaming in utter terror!

143
00:07:05,792 --> 00:07:07,394
Joseph: Astounding.

144
00:07:07,427 --> 00:07:10,563
You gotta wonder who or what
he shot at with that gun.

145
00:07:10,597 --> 00:07:11,865
What exactly happened?

146
00:07:11,899 --> 00:07:13,501
Kakyoin: Didn’t anyone here
see anything?

147
00:07:13,534 --> 00:07:14,769
No one’s stopped to help.

148
00:07:14,801 --> 00:07:16,970
Excuse me! Ma’am, wait!

149
00:07:17,004 --> 00:07:19,974
Someone has died here!
Please call the police!

150
00:07:23,944 --> 00:07:25,979
♪

151
00:07:26,013 --> 00:07:27,181
( Gasps )

152
00:07:31,618 --> 00:07:34,087
Woman: Pardon me, young man.

153
00:07:34,121 --> 00:07:38,058
My boils
seem to be festering today.

154
00:07:38,091 --> 00:07:41,928
My apologies.
You had a question.

155
00:07:41,962 --> 00:07:43,931
What was it that you needed?

156
00:07:43,964 --> 00:07:45,599
( Kakyoin gasps )

157
00:07:45,632 --> 00:07:47,868
I asked if you could
please call the police, ma’am.

158
00:07:47,901 --> 00:07:49,770
Woman: The police?

159
00:07:49,803 --> 00:07:52,773
What would I do that for?

160
00:07:52,806 --> 00:07:54,574
Kakyoin: Look!

161
00:07:54,608 --> 00:07:56,810
That man’s dead.

162
00:07:56,844 --> 00:08:00,147
Woman: Hmm.

163
00:08:00,180 --> 00:08:01,848
Someone is dead, you say?

164
00:08:01,882 --> 00:08:04,451
How terribly unfortunate.

165
00:08:04,484 --> 00:08:07,153
I’m not sure if there is
anything I can do about that.

166
00:08:07,187 --> 00:08:09,823
Kakyoin: I already asked you
to call the police twice.

167
00:08:09,857 --> 00:08:12,159
Woman: Of course.
Call the police.

168
00:08:12,192 --> 00:08:14,027
I think you did say that.

169
00:08:14,061 --> 00:08:15,829
Well, good day, sir.

170
00:08:15,863 --> 00:08:17,998
My boils are infected.

171
00:08:18,031 --> 00:08:21,868
They are so itchy,
so terribly itchy.

172
00:08:21,902 --> 00:08:22,903
( Kakyoin gags )

173
00:08:24,004 --> 00:08:25,472
( Gasping )

174
00:08:25,506 --> 00:08:28,476
What is with the people
in this town?

175
00:08:28,509 --> 00:08:30,444
There’s a man
lying dead in the street,

176
00:08:30,477 --> 00:08:33,480
and nobody seems even
the slightest bit concerned.

177
00:08:33,514 --> 00:08:34,648
( Bird squawks )

178
00:08:34,681 --> 00:08:36,550
Didn’t they hear the gunshot?

179
00:08:36,583 --> 00:08:39,052
Nobody’s doing anything.
It’s like they don’t even care.

180
00:08:39,086 --> 00:08:41,055
These people are more oblivious

181
00:08:41,088 --> 00:08:43,757
than the most jaded new yorker
or tokyoite.

182
00:08:43,790 --> 00:08:45,759
Jotaro: That dog...

183
00:08:47,194 --> 00:08:48,529
Polnareff: This blasted fog

184
00:08:48,562 --> 00:08:50,531
just keeps getting
thicker and thicker.

185
00:08:50,564 --> 00:08:52,499
Kakyoin: It’s almost
as if the fog

186
00:08:52,533 --> 00:08:53,834
is swallowing the town whole.

187
00:08:53,867 --> 00:08:55,202
Polnareff:
This is really creepy.

188
00:08:55,235 --> 00:08:56,770
Call me crazy,

189
00:08:56,803 --> 00:08:59,172
but doesn’t that part there
look like a skull?

190
00:09:11,752 --> 00:09:14,788
( Skull laughs )

191
00:09:14,821 --> 00:09:16,656
Jotaro: What do you want to do?

192
00:09:16,690 --> 00:09:18,859
You don’t think
it could be the work

193
00:09:18,892 --> 00:09:20,627
of another stand user, do you?

194
00:09:20,661 --> 00:09:23,597
Joseph: Eh, probably not.
There’s no motive.

195
00:09:23,630 --> 00:09:25,799
Why would someone
who’s after us kill a man

196
00:09:25,833 --> 00:09:28,803
who has nothing to do with us
before we even got here?

197
00:09:28,836 --> 00:09:32,606
There’s no reason
for a stand user to kill him.

198
00:09:32,639 --> 00:09:33,840
Jotaro: Who knows?

199
00:09:33,874 --> 00:09:36,210
The way he died
is obviously unnatural.

200
00:09:36,243 --> 00:09:38,946
Let’s examine the body
before the police come.

201
00:09:38,979 --> 00:09:40,848
Just try not to touch it.

202
00:09:40,881 --> 00:09:42,015
Joseph: Right.

203
00:09:44,651 --> 00:09:45,919
This might be something.

204
00:09:45,953 --> 00:09:48,622
It appears he was traveling,
too, just like us.

205
00:09:48,655 --> 00:09:51,825
He has bus and train tickets
in his pocket.

206
00:09:51,859 --> 00:09:54,028
And he looks like
he might be Indian.

207
00:09:54,061 --> 00:09:55,829
He’s carrying
Indian money on him.

208
00:09:55,863 --> 00:09:58,899
I’m guessing
he’s not from this town.

209
00:09:58,932 --> 00:10:00,233
Oh?

210
00:10:00,267 --> 00:10:01,769
♪

211
00:10:01,802 --> 00:10:02,870
Look at this wound.

212
00:10:02,903 --> 00:10:04,671
He’s got a gaping hole here,

213
00:10:04,705 --> 00:10:06,273
right in his upper chest.

214
00:10:06,306 --> 00:10:08,275
This must be what killed him.

215
00:10:08,308 --> 00:10:10,777
Jotaro: Hang on. Why isn’t
there any blood coming out?

216
00:10:10,811 --> 00:10:12,246
With a fatal chest wound
this big,

217
00:10:12,279 --> 00:10:15,682
there should be blood
gushing everywhere.

218
00:10:15,716 --> 00:10:17,585
Unless, of course...

219
00:10:17,618 --> 00:10:19,086
This is no ordinary murder.

220
00:10:19,119 --> 00:10:21,788
Looks like things
are about to get messy.

221
00:10:21,822 --> 00:10:23,957
We’ve gotta
get to the bottom of this.

222
00:10:23,991 --> 00:10:25,292
It’s time to search him.

223
00:10:25,325 --> 00:10:26,893
Take off his clothes.

224
00:10:27,995 --> 00:10:29,029
( All gasp )

225
00:10:30,197 --> 00:10:32,633
Polnareff:
What happened to his body?!

226
00:10:32,666 --> 00:10:35,035
There are tons of holes
all over this guy!

227
00:10:35,068 --> 00:10:38,004
He’s like that cartoon cheese
you see on "Tom and Jerry"!

228
00:10:38,038 --> 00:10:40,040
Joseph: And there’s
not a drop of blood

229
00:10:40,073 --> 00:10:41,841
anywhere near those wounds.

230
00:10:41,875 --> 00:10:43,744
How on earth
was this man killed?

231
00:10:43,777 --> 00:10:45,245
What does all of this mean?

232
00:10:45,279 --> 00:10:46,847
Jotaro: Be careful.

233
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:49,116
If there wasn’t
a stand user here before,

234
00:10:49,149 --> 00:10:51,618
you can bet
there’s one here now.

235
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:54,989
Joseph: Everyone,
get in the car!

236
00:10:55,022 --> 00:10:56,323
We’re leaving this town now!

237
00:10:56,356 --> 00:10:58,191
( Yells ) What the--

238
00:10:58,225 --> 00:11:00,027
all: Hmm?

239
00:11:00,060 --> 00:11:02,229
Joseph: Impossible!

240
00:11:02,262 --> 00:11:03,830
This isn’t the car!

241
00:11:03,864 --> 00:11:06,367
Oh, no!

242
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:09,803
( Yells ) Hermit purple!

243
00:11:11,772 --> 00:11:13,774
( Grunting )

244
00:11:15,776 --> 00:11:18,145
( Yells )

245
00:11:18,178 --> 00:11:19,813
Jotaro: Hey, old man...

246
00:11:19,847 --> 00:11:21,949
What in the hell are you doing?

247
00:11:21,982 --> 00:11:22,950
You’re crazy.

248
00:11:22,983 --> 00:11:24,751
( Joseph sighs )

249
00:11:24,785 --> 00:11:26,186
Huh? Oh, no!

250
00:11:26,220 --> 00:11:28,189
What do you mean,
what am I doing?

251
00:11:28,222 --> 00:11:30,091
The car was right here
just minute ago.

252
00:11:30,123 --> 00:11:31,925
Polnareff: Huh?
What are you talking about?

253
00:11:31,959 --> 00:11:33,961
We just parked the car
over there and walked.

254
00:11:33,994 --> 00:11:35,162
Joseph: What?!

255
00:11:35,195 --> 00:11:37,898
But just now,
I could have sworn that--

256
00:11:37,931 --> 00:11:39,166
( gasps )

257
00:11:39,199 --> 00:11:41,768
♪

258
00:11:41,802 --> 00:11:43,170
